PROGRAM main_1
VAR
//Problem1: Start from input1, go clockwise(out1) reset from input 3. To have sufficient time to stop, the Reset button will remain 
//active for 3s from Tof_0. The condition to reset out1 is that out1 has to be active, and out2 has to deactivate. 
//The condition to active out1 is out2 has to deactivate, reset for out1 and out2 has to deactive. The same thing for out2 go for counterclockwise


//Problem2 :Start from input1, it will active Tof_2 for 5 seconds -> run out1 from RS_0 for 5 seconds. And out1 connect to ToN_0, so it 
//will hold ton_0 for 5s at the same time. After hold ton_0 for 5s, it will active tof_3 (hold 3s to active ton_1 -> active tof_4 to run 
//out2 for 4s) )and tof_7 (reset rs_0-> turn off out1) at the same time. So tof3 and ton1 is use for stop out1 for 3s.
//After out2 run FOR 4S, it will active ton2 ->reset  out2 AND tof5 active AND hold 3S TO active ton3 (3S stop FOR out2). After ton3 
//active it will start the loop again because it connects TO set OF rs0.
//Condition to start out1 is non of them(out1,out2) is reseting(cooldown), input3 is not press
//Condition to reset out1 is out1 is running and out 2 is not running, input3 is pressed.
//Same condition to reset out2


//Problem3: Input1 start sr7 TO run out1. Sensor1 active will stop out1 AND active tof6 FOR 3S AND hold ton4 FOR 3S 
//(3s break after change direction) -> out2 run. Sensor 2 active will reset out1 and do the same thing as sensor 1 to run out1
//Condition TO run out1, out2 BY sensor is only 1 sensor is active AT the same TIME. Sr6 AND sr4 are use TO make sure out1, 
//out1 are only active by sensor after we start out1 with input1. 
//Condition under input1 is to make sure input1 cannot affect tonthe process when changing direction by sensors.
//Condition to reset is same as problem 1.


	//IMPORTANCE: ADD NEGATION TO ALL INPUT 3 BEFORE RUN IN REAL PLC. Deactive other problems when run one.
